@param string $prepend An optional non-value to prepend to the menu eg. '**&amp;nbsp;**'.  This is used for select menus when you would like a blank option up top.

@example

```php
$form->menu('gender', array(
'M' => 'Male',
'F' => 'Female',
)); // A radio menu

